SpiceSynth includes or depends on the following third-party software:

================================================================================
Nuked-OPL3
================================================================================

Description:  Cycle-accurate OPL3 (YMF262) emulator
Version:      1.8
Author:       Nuke.YKT
Copyright:    Copyright (C) 2013-2020 Nuke.YKT
License:      GNU Lesser General Public License v2.1 or later (LGPL-2.1-or-later)
Source:       https://github.com/nukeykt/Nuked-OPL3
Location:     external dependency via github.com/jebbisson/spice-opl3-nuked

SpiceSynth no longer vendors the Nuked-OPL3 source directly. The concrete OPL
implementation now lives in the sibling `spice-opl3-nuked` module, which owns
the LGPL-covered wrapper and upstream vendored source.

================================================================================
DMXOPL
================================================================================

Description:  YMF262-enhanced FM patch set for Doom and source ports
Author:       sneakernets
Copyright:    Copyright (c) 2017 sneakernets
License:      MIT License
Source:       https://github.com/sneakernets/DMXOPL
Location:     op2/GENMIDI.op2

The DMXOPL GENMIDI bank file is embedded in the op2 package and provides
General MIDI instrument definitions (128 melodic + 47 percussion) for OPL2/OPL3
FM synthesis. The file is included unmodified under the MIT license.

================================================================================
AdPlug
================================================================================

Description:  AdLib sound player library
Authors:      Simon Peter, Torbjorn Andersson, Johannes Schickel (ScummVM)
Copyright:    Copyright (C) 1999-2024 Simon Peter et al.
License:      GNU Lesser General Public License v2.1 or later (LGPL-2.1-or-later)
Source:       https://github.com/adplug/adplug
Location:     external dependency via github.com/jebbisson/spice-adl-adplug

SpiceSynth is in the process of moving ADL-derived functionality into the
separate `spice-adl-adplug` module so the LGPL-derived code has a clearer
repository boundary.
